### FastVocab API - Collections Management Test
@baseUrl = https://localhost:5001/api
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get all collections
GET {{baseUrl}}/collections
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 2. Get collection by ID (replace with actual ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/collections/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 3. Get collection with lists
GET {{baseUrl}}/collections/1/lists
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 4. Create new collection
POST {{baseUrl}}/collections
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "TOEIC Vocabulary",
  "description": "Essential words for TOEIC exam",
  "targetAudience": "Students preparing for TOEIC",
  "difficultyLevel": "B1",
  "imageUrl": "https://example.com/toeic.jpg"
}

### 5. Update collection (replace ID with actual)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/collections/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Updated TOEIC Vocabulary",
  "description": "Updated description",
  "targetAudience": "TOEIC candidates",
  "difficultyLevel": "B2",
  "imageUrl": "https://example.com/updated.jpg",
  "isHiding": false
}

### 6. Toggle collection visibility
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/collections/1/visibility
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 7. Delete collection
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/collections/1

### 8. Create word list in collection (replace collection ID)
POST {{baseUrl}}/collections/1/lists
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "collectionId": 1,
  "name": "Lesson 1: Business Terms",
  "imageUrl": "https://example.com/lesson1.jpg"
}

### 9. Validation test - Create collection with empty name
POST {{baseUrl}}/collections
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "",
  "description": "Test"
}

### 10. Duplicate name test
POST {{baseUrl}}/collections
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "TOEIC Vocabulary",
  "description": "Duplicate"
}
